==English==

===Etymology===
{{etyl|la|en}} {{term|pyra||pyre, funeral pile|lang=la}}, from {{etyl|grc|en}} {{term|πυρά|lang=grc}}, from {{term|πῦρ||fire|lang=grc}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{m|ine-pro|*péh₂ur}}.

{{etymtwin|lang=en}} {{term|fire|lang=en}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ˈpaɪɚ/|lang=en}}
* {{rhymes|aɪə(r)|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A [[funeral]] [[pile]]; a combustible heap on which [[corpse]]s are burned.
#:* For nine long nights, through all the dusky air, The '''pyres''' thick flaming shot a dismal glare. - [[Homer]] Iliad, p. 31
# Any [[heap]] or [[pile]] of [[combustible]]s.

